-- Marfrig CEO Increases Stake in Company for Fifth Straight Month
-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 2012-08-11T13:43:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-11/marfrig-ceo-increases-stake-in-company-for-fifth-straight-month.html
Marfrig Alimentos SA (MRFG3)  founder and
Chief Executive Officer Marcos Antonio Molina boosted his stake
in the company for a fifth consecutive month.  Molina increased his stake to 48.8 percent in July from
48.6 percent a month earlier, according to a statement
yesterday. Since February, he has spent about 74.6 million reais
($37 million) buying shares, according to previous regulatory
filings. He held 43.5 percent of the company a year ago.  Marfrig shares  dropped  41 percent in the past two years,
more than the 12 percent slide of the Bovespa stock index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in Sao Paulo at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
